OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBristol mayor vote: City   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdecides to abolish mayor   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpost                       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Voters in Bristol have decided to      
OL,6, abolish its directly elected mayor     
OL,7, following a referendum.                
OL,9,FThe city was given the choice of a     
OL,10,Fmayor or a committee system in which   
OL,11,Fdecisions are made by groups of        
OL,12,Fcouncillors.                           
OL,14,FSome 56,113 voted to scrap the post.   
OL,15,FThe turnout for the referendum was 29%.
OL,17,FBristol currently has a Labour mayor,  
OL,18,FMarvin Rees, who will hold the position
OL,19,Funtil 2024. He was preceded by         
OL,20,Findependent George Ferguson.           
